Oh, God.

256
00:17:20,442 --> 00:17:23,195
- Wow! Is that Michelle?
- Yep.

257
00:17:23,445 --> 00:17:26,031
I've not seen her since
high-school graduation.

258
00:17:26,281 --> 00:17:30,786
Oh, my God, that night
she got so dru...

259
00:17:31,703 --> 00:17:32,996
Emotional.

260
00:17:33,246 --> 00:17:35,665
You know, she's having another baby.

261
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:39,878
- I thought she just had one.
- No, no. Henry's almost 2.

262
00:17:40,128 --> 00:17:44,091
And he's talking
and everything. Here.

263
00:17:44,341 --> 00:17:48,178
The other day he told me he liked me
better than his other grandpa.

264
00:17:48,428 --> 00:17:53,308
In all fairness, his other
grandpa's a drunk, but still...

265
00:17:54,643 --> 00:17:57,896
You're a grandpa.

266
00:18:05,821 --> 00:18:07,864
Are we nuts here?

267
00:18:08,115 --> 00:18:10,909
I don't know. Maybe.

268
00:18:11,159 --> 00:18:15,163
I mean, I'm dating a man
whose pool I once peed in.

269
00:18:15,413 --> 00:18:18,375
I didn't need to know that.

270
00:18:18,625 --> 00:18:21,211
I guess 21 years is a lot.

271
00:18:21,461 --> 00:18:27,717
I mean, hell, I'm a whole person
who can drink older than you.

272
00:18:36,143 --> 00:18:40,647
So maybe we should just...

273
00:18:42,023 --> 00:18:44,526
Maybe...

274
00:18:47,479 --> 00:18:50,023
Wow.

275
00:18:51,232 --> 00:18:52,567
This really sucks.

276
00:18:52,817 --> 00:18:56,696
Yeah, it sure does.

277
00:19:12,796 --> 00:19:16,007
We don't really have to decide
anything right now, do we?

278
00:19:16,257 --> 00:19:19,761
No, there's no rush or anything.

279
00:19:20,011 --> 00:19:25,058
- Pizza delivery!
- Oh, I'm gonna kill those guys!

280
00:19:28,186 --> 00:19:30,105
I'm done.

281
00:19:30,355 --> 00:19:33,483
Yeah, well, you know what?
So is Sorentino's.

282
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:36,986
I'm sorry.
Why don't we find someplace else?

283
00:19:37,237 --> 00:19:40,657
It's late. Everything will be closed.
We'll do it another night.

284
00:19:40,907 --> 00:19:42,283
No, no, we won't.

285
00:19:42,534 --> 00:19:44,327
We won't?

286
00:19:44,577 --> 00:19:46,204
Come on.

287
00:19:46,454 --> 00:19:49,916
Okay, that's dead, right?

288
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:52,293
What are we doing?

289
00:19:52,544 --> 00:19:57,590
- Do you want Cranapple or Cran-Grape?
- Grape.

290
00:19:58,341 --> 00:19:59,843
Okay, now...

291
00:20:00,093 --> 00:20:02,804
...sit.

292
00:20:06,015 --> 00:20:09,018
Oh, my God!

293
00:20:09,269 --> 00:20:14,274
<i>Billions of years ago,
Earth was only...</i>

294
00:20:14,691 --> 00:20:17,277
Sorry.

295
00:20:21,072 --> 00:20:23,116
So what are we looking at?

296
00:20:23,366 --> 00:20:27,662
Well, you see that little cluster
of stars next to the big one?

297
00:20:27,912 --> 00:20:30,707
That is Ursa Major.

298
00:20:30,957 --> 00:20:35,545
- Really?
- No idea. It could be.

299
00:20:37,213 --> 00:20:39,841
Listen, I'm sorry
I had to work tonight.

300
00:20:40,091 --> 00:20:41,968
Oh, that's okay.

301
00:20:42,218 --> 00:20:44,888
You were worth the wait.

302
00:20:45,138 --> 00:20:48,891
And I don't just mean tonight.

303
00:20:57,025 --> 00:20:59,068
You're not laughing.

304
00:20:59,319 --> 00:21:03,072
This time it's not so funny.

305
00:21:34,604 --> 00:21:37,065
Oh, God!

306
00:21:37,231 --> 00:21:38,399
Honey?

307
00:21:38,649 --> 00:21:40,943
That's okay.

308
00:21:41,194 --> 00:21:42,945
What?

309
00:21:43,196 --> 00:21:47,742
Oh, no. You just rolled
over the juice box.

310
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:57,794
Thank God!

311
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:28,991
Hey, you.

312
00:22:33,788 --> 00:22:36,833
I can't believe I'm waking up
next to you.

313
00:22:37,083 --> 00:22:40,795
I know. It is pretty unbel...

314
00:22:41,838 --> 00:22:45,258
We're not alone.

315
00:23:12,016 --> 00:23:15,645
Is that the fire alarm?

316
00:23:19,107 --> 00:23:22,902
It's not warm yet.
We still have time.

317
00:23:23,152 --> 00:23:27,156
- Cool.
- <i>Yeah, yeah. Cool!</i>
